This, combined with the main article, absolutely fascinates me. If I could have one SCP on this site exist in real life, as far as I've read, I would choose Able. That may seem strange, but the reason is that I wish I could talk to him - with safety measures in place, of course. I'd like to understand him better. I mean, the article says at one point that he's  - he just kills without any inhibitions, with no empathy for his enemies, which is ideal in a soldier. He also seems to have a strong sense of a warrior's honor - his respect for the unnamed agent, and his comments about said agent deserving to die in direct combat, suggested to me that 1) he believes the best, most honorable way to die is in battle, and 2) he honors a worthy opponent. I'd like to be able to talk to him…no pun intended.

There's just one thing I'm confused about: I thought that Cain was the bad guy, and Abel was the victim? Still, this is one of my favorite SCP's. +1!





