There are so many things wrong with this post it isn't even funny.

The main thing being that for the majority of Christians, Genesis 1-15 (that would be including Cain and Abel) is completely fictional anyway. It's a myth, written as a counter to other common myths of the day, most specifically the Enuma Elish and the Epic of Gilgamesh. What's important is the meaning, not the contents of the story itself, because it's not meant to be taken as historical fact. Cain and Able's articles hinge on the idea of  which is fine and good, but please remember:

THIS IS FICTION. IT IS A FICTIONAL SHORT STORY ON THE INTERNET, MEANT FOR ENTERTAINMENT, NOT FOR THE IMPARTING OF MORAL LESSONS. IT IS NOT A RELIABLE REPLACEMENT FOR THEOLOGICAL, PHILOSOPHICAL, LITERARY OR HISTORICAL STUDY OF FICTIONAL STORIES MEANT TO IMPART MORAL LESSONS OR HISTORICAL ACCOUNTS OF THE SAME PURPOSE. 

